# Riverside Chatbot CLI App

This is a standalone CLI version of the Riverside Books chatbot, created as a separate project so the original `Riverside Chatbot solution` folder stays untouched.

The default experience is now a simple full-screen TUI for Riverside Books, with a book-themed sidebar, chat transcript, and fixed input box.

## Quick start

From this folder:

```powershell
cd "C:\Users\sossi\OneDrive\Desktop\agent builder workspace\CLI app"
python -m pip install -r requirements.txt
python main.py
```

Ask a question in the input bar and press `Enter`. Press `Ctrl+C` to quit.

## Windows launcher

From PowerShell in this folder, you can also run:

```powershell
.\riverside-chatbot.cmd
```

That wrapper avoids any PATH setup.

## Plain CLI fallback

If you want the older line-by-line terminal mode instead of the full-screen UI:

```powershell
python main.py --plain
```

## Install as a command

If you want a reusable terminal command:

```powershell
cd "C:\Users\sossi\OneDrive\Desktop\agent builder workspace\CLI app"
python -m pip install -e .
```

If `riverside-chatbot` is not recognized afterward, your Python Scripts folder is not on PATH in the current shell. In that case, keep using `python main.py`, `python -m riverside_cli_app.cli`, or `.\riverside-chatbot.cmd`.

## Useful options

```powershell
python main.py --help
python main.py --debug
python main.py --lexical-only
python main.py --plain
python main.py --faq-path .\riverside_cli_app\runtime_assets\faqs.json
.\riverside-chatbot.cmd --lexical-only
```

## Notes

- The first semantic run may download the sentence-transformer model.
- If you want to avoid that, run `python main.py --lexical-only`.
- Inside the TUI, `F2` toggles matcher mode, `F3` focuses the input box, and `Ctrl+L` clears the chat.
